20
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:38,620
<font color=9015e7>COLD CASE
Season 6 Episode 23</font>

21
00:02:39,290 --> 00:02:41,330
And what day is it ?

22
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,570
Saturday.

23
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,170
Any blurred vision, nausea ?

24
00:02:46,330 --> 00:02:47,390
No.

25
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:50,290
No signs of hypothermia, but you
took a pretty good shot to the head.

26
00:02:50,330 --> 00:02:51,590
Might have a concussion.

27
00:02:51,591 --> 00:02:53,991
Going to need to run a couple of tests...
CT scan, for one...

28
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:56,290
- and we'll follow that up with...
- How long is that going to take ?

29
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:59,280
The tech will be down in a couple
of minutes to bring you upstairs...

30
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,810
if they're not too backed up.

31
00:03:00,890 --> 00:03:03,640
Either way,you're going to need to
take it easy for a while,Detective,

32
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,760
and...

33
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,240
Hey, where you going, Lil ?

34
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,770
The doc released you already ?

35
00:03:12,850 --> 00:03:15,750
Oh, did all the tests and
came back fine.

36
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:18,540
They haven't even dredged your
squad car out of Neshaminy Creek yet.

37
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:20,700
Did CSU find anything at the scene ?

38
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:22,720
Skid marks from the vehicle
that ran you off the road.

39
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,410
Will, Nick and Kat are searching
PMI's campus

40
00:03:24,411 --> 00:03:25,611
for a car with body damage.

41
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:27,060
Lil !

42
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,520
It was Cadet Lawrence Gardner,
boss.

43
00:03:28,550 --> 00:03:30,190
He wrote that sword hate mail,

44
00:03:30,191 --> 00:03:31,691
attacked Kate Butler
in the shower.

45
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:33,700
- He wanted her gone.
- Whoa, slow down, Lil.

46
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:36,400
No, I'm fine. I'm telling you.

47
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,840
We know where Lawrence
is now ?

48
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,680
Scotty went to PMI this morning
to pick him up.

49
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,370
He wasn't in his room,
anywhere on campus.

50
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:47,450
We have broadcasts all over
the region looking for him now.

51
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,660
Got to be the same guy
that ran me off the road.

52
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:52,880
Now, let me drive you home.
At least get a change of clothes.

53
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,960
Got everything I need in my locker.

54
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:57,090
Hey, guys.

55
00:03:57,210 --> 00:03:58,310
Lil.

56
00:03:58,390 --> 00:04:00,770
- Hey, how you doing ?
- I'm fine.

57
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:02,880
You'd do anything to get out of
that bucket of bolts, wouldn't you ?

58
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,030
What do you got ?

59
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:06,190
Picked up Lawrence's files
when I was up there.

60
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,430
Reason he's still a senior :
he took six months off

61
00:04:08,431 --> 00:04:10,131
two weeks after Kate disappeared.

62
00:04:10,170 --> 00:04:11,510
Mom said he had mono.

63
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:13,310
The oldest excuse in the book.

64
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:16,530
What about Keith Henderson,
black cadet who said he was on tours ?

65
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:18,510
Yeah,checked the tours
and confinements lists.

66
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:19,700
Kid was on it.

67
00:04:19,701 --> 00:04:22,001
The swipe card says
he never left campus.

68
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,750
Doesn't add up.
Barracks sign-out log says

69
00:04:23,751 --> 00:04:25,651
he left the dorm same time Kate did.

70
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:27,700
That's 'cause the log was copied.

71
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:29,340
Found it last night in the diner.

72
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:32,370
November 15, '05,
the night Kate disappeared.

73
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,210
Check this one out : November 1.

74
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:37,600
Names, signatures, times.
Everything's the same.

75
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,010
Same damn sign-out log.
Only the date's be changed.

76
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,640
Made it look like
Kate didn't come back.

77
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:44,110
The truth is, she never even left.

78
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,040
So, who doctored these logs ?

79
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:47,790
Lilly.

80
00:04:52,570 --> 00:04:53,860
Today's not the day.

81
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:56,240
Only place I know where to find you.

82
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,210
You get the letter I sent ?

83
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:02,520
You can't fix everything
with a damned letter, Dad.

84
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,570
You at least read it ?

85
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:10,880
Lilly ?

86
00:05:21,830 --> 00:05:23,670
Your turn, pook.

87
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:26,220
I know.

88
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,770
Lilly...

89
00:05:31,871 --> 00:05:34,071
I have to go do some things.

90
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,240
It means that I...

91
00:05:37,941 --> 00:05:40,941
I may have to be gone a while.

92
00:05:41,610 --> 00:05:43,620
Where are you going ?

93
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,970
Don't know yet.

94
00:05:46,090 --> 00:05:48,050
With Mommy ?

95
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,770
No, no, I don't... I don't think so.
Probably not.

96
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,710
Who's going to sleep by her ?

97
00:05:57,810 --> 00:06:03,820
Well, sometimes mommies and daddies,
they don't sleep by each other.

98
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,900
Which way can I move
my knight ?

99
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:15,490
L-move,two and one.

100
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:18,910
But if you take my pawn,
I'll take your knight with my rook.

101
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,420
Or you could do that.

102
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:30,410
You really are a smart kid.

103
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:40,830
Lilly.

104
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:44,670
What's the matter ?

105
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,900
- Are you okay ?
- I got to get back.

106
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:49,990
Celeste.

107
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:53,600
My wife's name.

108
00:06:53,670 --> 00:06:55,370
Been married 22 years.

109
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:58,620
We have a daughter, Maggie,
and a son, Finn.

110
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:01,610
They want to meet you.

111
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:04,310
Lil.

112
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:09,050
John Stillman.

113
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,170
Paul Cooper.

114
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:14,070
I didn't mean to interrupt.

115
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,080
You're not.

116
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,810
I got to go.

117
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,170
We found the car that
ran you off the road.

118
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,980
It's on the PMI campus.

119
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,680
Passenger-side mirror is busted.

120
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,050
Dent, front right side.

121
00:07:29,130 --> 00:07:32,020
Paint transfer from another car.
CSU tech took a sample.

122
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,360
Looks like yours.

123
00:07:33,470 --> 00:07:36,390
Said the treads looked good
for the skid marks at the scene.

124
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,920
Is it the car that hit you ?

125
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,150
All I saw were the headlights.

126
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:42,370
Glad you're okay.

127
00:07:42,450 --> 00:07:43,870
Thanks.

128
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:46,020
PMI staffer said
it's a campus car.

129
00:07:46,021 --> 00:07:47,221
Tow squad's on its way.

130
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,450
Belongs to the school ?

131
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:51,150
We just got to find out who had
access and where the keys are.

132
00:07:51,350 --> 00:07:53,100
Time to shut this campus down.

133
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:55,140
Trap a rat in his hole.

134
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:59,460
DEFCON One in effect, Detectives.

135
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:02,420
Front gate is closed.Every door
with a handle or hinge,locked down.

136
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:04,040
Who are the campus cars for ?

137
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,160
We make them available to
administrators who may need them.

138
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,610
What about students ?

139
00:08:07,730 --> 00:08:10,200
- Only senior aides.
- Lawrence Gardner.

140
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,080
He a senior aide ?

141
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:17,471
Assaulting and killing Kate Butler,
running a cop off the road.

142
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:19,220
Those are some serious accusations
you're making.

143
00:08:19,221 --> 00:08:21,121
Suburban with the damage.

144
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,890
Was Lawrence using it ?

145
00:08:25,950 --> 00:08:28,730
He was picking up a football
recruit at the airport yesterday.

146
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:32,260
Still has the keys.

147
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:35,680
Lawrence have access to the
barracks sign-out logs in '05 ?

148
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,530
Lawrence's always done his best
to serve the school.

149
00:08:37,570 --> 00:08:39,770
Just answer the question.

150
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:43,480
He was Echo Company clerk.

151
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:47,330
Why did Lawrence take a six-month
leave of absence, December '05 ?

152
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,630
Wasn't mono, was it, Moe ?

153
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:51,790
Fatigue.

154
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:54,750
"Fatigue." You saying the kid
had some kind of breakdown ?

155
00:08:56,590 --> 00:08:57,750
Looking back...

156
00:08:57,951 --> 00:08:59,651
a few days before
she disappeared,

157
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,100
it all starts to make sense.

158
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,790
Fight till you drop.

159
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:07,570
You go down, you die.

160
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:10,420
Someone will take care
of your girl. Understood ?

161
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,420
Sir, yes, sir !

162
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:17,280
Now, which one of you chuckleheads thinks
he can take Cadet Lawrence,

163
00:09:17,281 --> 00:09:19,381
best pugil stick in Echo Company ?

164
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,000
No one wants to man up ?

165
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,210
I'd like a shot, sir.

166
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:29,660
Cadet Butler... you a man ?

167
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,480
No, sir. But I'd like a shot, sir.

168
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,850
Think you're special, Butler ?

169
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,550
Is that how you see yourself,
special as a snowflake ?

170
00:09:35,590 --> 00:09:37,670
Sir, I'm no snowflake, sir.

171
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,730
Step up, Maxipad.
Don't say I didn't warn you.

172
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:43,970
Lawrence, take no prisoners.

173
00:09:44,010 --> 00:09:45,580
Yes, sir.

174
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,120
Hit him, Kate...
that's right.

175
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,690
Come on ! Come on, Lawrence.

176
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:58,300
Don't let a girl kick your ass.

177
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,330
Come on, Lawrence...
don't let her get you.

178
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,100
Knock that bitch down !

179
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,050
Get up, Kate... come on !

180
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,440
Take her down, Lawrence.

181
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:23,240
Don't you ever come near me again.

182
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:27,841
<i>"Alive" by Pearl Jam.</i>

183
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:35,550
Girl was tougher than I thought.

184
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:37,260
Saying she was out for revenge ?

185
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:39,860
Didn't know about the
assault at the time.

186
00:10:39,970 --> 00:10:41,980
Well, Lawrence didn't walk out
the front gate.

187
00:10:42,020 --> 00:10:43,980
He's got to be holed up
somewhere on campus.

188
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:47,190
There's only one room in
the barracks with a lock.

189
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,580
Where's the key to Kate's room ?

190
00:10:51,981 --> 00:10:53,681
........

191
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:01,370
Police ! Open up.

192
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:10,860
Get him down.

193
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:16,110
Forget it... he's gone.

194
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:23,870
Key to the room.

195
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,970
And keys to the Suburban.

196
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:32,130
Son of a bitch.

197
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:34,640
Look at the rope.

198
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:36,290
Standard slipknot.

199
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:37,590
It's on the right side.

200
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:39,550
How did he tie it himself ?

201
00:11:39,630 --> 00:11:41,400
Lawrence was left-handed.

202
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:47,050
Knot should be on the other side.

203
00:11:47,090 --> 00:11:49,680
Rope's up under the chin.
Like he was lifted up.

204
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:51,920
Did it himself, it would've dug
into his Adam's apple.

205
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,230
Marks on the back of the neck.

206
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:57,100
This kid didn't kill himself.

207
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:59,570
Someone did it for him.

208
00:12:27,469 --> 00:12:28,669
Face front.

209
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:35,770
Lilly ?

210
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:38,360
You all right ?

211
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:41,110
Number three.

212
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,900
You sure ?

213
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:45,510
Yes.

214
00:12:45,590 --> 00:12:47,390
It was him.

215
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:50,100
Number three, John.

216
00:12:56,930 --> 00:12:59,640
You're a brave girl, Lilly Rush.

217
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:01,250
Who are you ?

218
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:03,640
John Stillman.

219
00:13:04,940 --> 00:13:07,970
Detective Stillman's the one
who caught the man that hurt you.

220
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:10,600
My mother said it was too late.

221
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:15,940
Long as you ask the right questions,
never too late.

222
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,730
Lil ?

223
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,400
Sure you're okay ?

224
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,930
- Tired, that's all.
- I asked around.

225
00:13:29,970 --> 00:13:32,920
Lawrence spent his share of time
in the chapel. Religious type.

226
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,610
Explains all that biblical hate mail.

227
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,990
Hiding her nakedness
from the sight of God.

228
00:13:37,030 --> 00:13:40,560
Going to talk to the chaplain. See if
he confided in him about anything.

229
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:44,330
Campus lockdown came
a little too late.

230
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,230
Coroner thinks Lawrence might've
been killed some time last night.

231
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:49,240
Get back to your duties.

232
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,770
All hail the commandant.

233
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:54,130
Detective Rush. I've just informed
Cadet Gardner's family.

234
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:55,930
Second homicide in four years.

235
00:13:56,010 --> 00:13:57,620
You got a PR disaster on your hands.

236
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,040
I was told this was a suicide.

237
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:01,870
Lawrence was dead
before he was hung.

238
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:05,190
Someone must've found out
we were looking at him.

239
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:07,840
- This happened last night ?
- That mean something you ?

240
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:11,060
Hank Butler came to see me.

241
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:14,090
He had been drinking.

242
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,310
You son of a bitch.

243
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,460
My daughter's gone.
Kate is gone.

244
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:22,280
- Hank, sit down.
- You were in charge, Lou.

245
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,380
I tried talking to her,
but she was her father's daughter.

246
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:27,030
She kept her own counsel.

247
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:29,150
Talk to her about what ?

248
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:32,240
A racking. May have gone too far.

249
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:35,180
Why didn't you call me ?

250
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:37,690
You said no special treatment.

251
00:14:38,691 --> 00:14:42,291
<i>"Man of the Hour" by Pearl Jam.</i>

252
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:45,540
What happened ?

253
00:14:49,780 --> 00:14:54,290
Couple of weeks before she disappeared,
I think she may have been assaulted.

254
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,820
I want the name of every
cadre in Echo Company.

255
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:03,730
Now.

256
00:15:05,420 --> 00:15:07,970
Hank and I were knobs together.
We graduated the same year.

257
00:15:08,010 --> 00:15:10,290
And you gave him those names ?

258
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:13,110
He would've found out anyway.

259
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:15,310
Lawrence Gardner on that list ?

260
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:17,940
What time did he leave your office ?

261
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:19,280
Little after midnight.

262
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:23,520
I assumed he went
straight home, but now...

263
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:27,550
Forgot this last time you were here.

264
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:31,670
I heard about a guy,
lost his PMI ring at boot camp.

265
00:15:32,070 --> 00:15:33,620
Ten year anniversary,

266
00:15:33,621 --> 00:15:36,621
his wife had a replacement made
to the exact specs.

267
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:39,010
Cadet number inside,
and whole nine.

268
00:15:39,090 --> 00:15:42,260
- Charlotte told you about that ?
- You used to love that school.

269
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,530
- It's hard to remember.
- How about last night ?

270
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:47,930
- Remember that, Hank ?
- Yeah, I do.

271
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,810
Had a date with a bottle.

272
00:15:49,890 --> 00:15:52,510
Was a terrible date.
Just what I wanted.

273
00:15:52,590 --> 00:15:54,390
The date go down at PMI ?

274
00:15:54,510 --> 00:15:57,610
Sallyport guard saw your car
leaving campus at 3:00 a.m.

275
00:15:57,670 --> 00:16:01,920
About the time Cadet
Lawrence Gardner was killed.

276
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:06,430
Eye for an eye, Hank ?

277
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:07,960
I didn't hurt anyone.

278
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:10,400
You find that son of a bitch
before we did ?

279
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:12,590
I know what I said.

280
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:14,050
But I saw the chapel.

281
00:16:14,130 --> 00:16:16,340
- The chapel, Hank ?
- Yeah.

282
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:17,830
And I asked God's forgiveness

283
00:16:17,831 --> 00:16:20,131
