the metal bar in her closet.

333
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,270
"Three good reasons
we should be together.

334
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:05,240
one : They'll never find out.

335
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,630
" "Two: None couldove you as much as Io.

336
00:19:07,740 --> 00:19:09,940
Three: can't live thout you."

337
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:12,660
- "J.F.A."
-  "J.F.A".

338
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:15,560
- James Addison ?
- James Frederick Addison.

339
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,730
Commandant asked him
to keep an eye on Kate.

340
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,730
Gives a whole new meaning to
"shine detail".

341
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:21,130
Kate decides to call it off.

342
00:19:21,210 --> 00:19:22,820
But he won't let her go.

343
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:26,100
Puts her in a footlocker instead.

344
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:38,490
Got Romeo in the box.
You ready ?

345
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,960
Be right there.

346
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,550
Son !Congratulations !

347
00:20:05,980 --> 00:20:07,940
Your mother and I are so proud of you.

348
00:20:15,370 --> 00:20:17,160
Hey, Lil, you coming or what ?

349
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:20,160
You see my dad come by
here a few minutes ago ?

350
00:20:21,380 --> 00:20:23,530
No. No.
Is everything all right ?

351
00:20:24,820 --> 00:20:26,310
Yeah. Yeah.

352
00:20:30,740 --> 00:20:33,510
Just trying to tie up
some loose ends, Lieutenant.

353
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:37,480
What you told us about Kate
being attacked in the showers.

354
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:40,790
- I told you everything I ow.
- Right, on shine detail.

355
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:43,580
She ever mention being romantically
involved with another cadet?

356
00:20:43,630 --> 00:20:45,090
No. She wasn't.

357
00:20:45,170 --> 00:20:46,510
Well, you seem pretty sure about that.

358
00:20:46,590 --> 00:20:49,650
She wouldn't risk violating
the non-fraternization policy.

359
00:20:49,730 --> 00:20:51,260
Would you ?

360
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:54,240
I don't know what you mean.

361
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:56,840
Found this love letter in her room.

362
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:58,680
It's your handwriting, Don Juan.

363
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:01,790
You didn't just watch out for
Cadet Butler. You took advantage of her.

364
00:21:01,870 --> 00:21:03,920
Senior cadet is a position of power.

365
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,680
She couldn't get rid
of you if she wanted to.

366
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,150
She wasn't getting rid of me.

367
00:21:07,151 --> 00:21:09,251
You knew about the assault,
that Lawrence was unstable.

368
00:21:09,290 --> 00:21:10,940
Told us about the barracks
sign-out log,

369
00:21:10,941 --> 00:21:12,741
the list of guards with sabers.

370
00:21:12,780 --> 00:21:14,360
You knew Lawrence would
look good for her murder.

371
00:21:14,390 --> 00:21:17,970
You string him up, case closed,
right, we all go home ?

372
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:22,190
Beautiful job.

373
00:21:22,270 --> 00:21:26,820
You just put the knot
on the wrong damn side.

374
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:28,550
I don't get it. I thought
Lawrence killed himself.

375
00:21:28,590 --> 00:21:31,650
Lawrence didn't kill himself, James.
Just like Kate didn't run away.

376
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:35,180
Give us three good reasons we
shouldn't lock your lying ass up.

377
00:21:42,790 --> 00:21:44,670
All right, so I liked her.

378
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:46,830
And when she didn't like you back ?

379
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,170
What did you do then,James?

380
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:50,300
I wrote her that letter.

381
00:21:50,370 --> 00:21:52,180
She doesn't give you the
answer you're looking for.

382
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:54,250
Try and convince her otherwise,
she says no...

383
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:56,880
No ! She felt the same way.

384
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:58,370
I know she did.

385
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,550
<i>"Given to Fly" by Pearl Jam.</i>

386
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:05,940
Cadet Butler ?

387
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:21,060
There's a million good reasons
we should be together,James.

388
00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:23,690
But I can't.

389
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:26,240
Not until after Recognition Day.

390
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,810
What's gonna change then?

391
00:22:27,890 --> 00:22:30,130
Won't be a knob anymore.

392
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:32,250
They won't treat you any different,
Kate. Trust me.

393
00:22:32,290 --> 00:22:34,510
The hell with them.I'm
not doing this for them.

394
00:22:35,650 --> 00:22:37,790
You're doing it 'cause of your old man.

395
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,730
Growing up,

396
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:46,340
my dad talked about this place
like the Earth revolved around it.

397
00:22:46,410 --> 00:22:49,200
But now, I'm doing it for me.

398
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:51,320
And the harder they push,
the harder I fight back.

399
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:54,070
That's the way you want to go about it,
it's gonna be a long four years.

400
00:22:54,430 --> 00:22:57,650
- I won that medal legit.
- Lots of guys won medals, Kate.

401
00:22:57,690 --> 00:22:59,530
Just 'cause you can hack it
doesn't mean they'll accept you.

402
00:22:59,570 --> 00:23:01,970
I can't make them like me.

403
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:05,740
They think you're some tight-ass grinder,
a barracks rat.

404
00:23:05,810 --> 00:23:07,620
You never go out, you never
even let them get to know you.

405
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:09,350
You don't think I want that ?

406
00:23:09,390 --> 00:23:10,730
I've never been invited.

407
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:12,810
I'm inviting you now.

408
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:16,180
You said it yourself.
They hate me.

409
00:23:16,930 --> 00:23:19,480
Well, then, let them see
the other side of you.

410
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,500
The side that I see.

411
00:23:22,740 --> 00:23:25,170
Don't just prove to them
that you can hack it.

412
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:27,960
Prove to them that you belong.

413
00:23:30,260 --> 00:23:32,890
I thought she was gonna come
out that night and meet me.

414
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:37,050
That maybe things could
change for Kate at the school.

415
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:38,320
But she never showed up ?

416
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,630
I didn't blame her.
I mean, the guys were tough.

417
00:23:41,650 --> 00:23:45,230
But no barracks rat ever
makes it through PMI.

418
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:46,720
Barracks rat ?

419
00:23:46,721 --> 00:23:48,621
Guys who hole up in the dorms
all weekend.

420
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:51,820
Too stressful a place.
You... you got to blow off some steam.

421
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:57,350
There's no way you can make it
through that school without friends.

422
00:23:59,150 --> 00:24:00,960
Excuse me.

423
00:24:05,340 --> 00:24:06,890
You all right ?

424
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:09,870
Freezing.
Who turned off the heat ?

425
00:24:09,871 --> 00:24:11,371
Cutbacks. Dropped the thermostat.

426
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,780
Do me favor.

427
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:15,650
Check the sign-out logs
for all of Kate's knob year.

428
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:19,120
Find the barracks rats, cadets
who never left on the weekends.

429
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:44,260
Ma'am ?

430
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,220
You wanted to see me,
Lieutenant ?

431
00:25:18,260 --> 00:25:21,330
I see you made the pinch
on that carjacking, Rush.

432
00:25:21,410 --> 00:25:23,900
Yes, Lieutenant. Had a lucky day.

433
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:26,100
You create your luck by hard work.

434
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:27,900
Well, if I was paying
more attention,

435
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:30,101
I might have caught the guy
before he got out onto the highway.

436
00:25:30,690 --> 00:25:32,770
You did well on the
detective's test, too.

437
00:25:32,850 --> 00:25:33,840
Looks like you'll make it next week.

438
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:37,130
Thank you,sir.Figure I'll
probably end up in East.

439
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:39,690
I have a few guys set to
retire next couple of years.

440
00:25:39,770 --> 00:25:44,080
I could use somebody with your
instincts and determination.

441
00:25:45,650 --> 00:25:47,090
Homicide ?

442
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:48,740
You interested ?

443
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:49,860
Of course, sir.

444
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,930
Well, learn your job at East,
do it right.

445
00:25:51,970 --> 00:25:54,710
I'll keep an eye out,
and we'll talk when the time comes.

446
00:25:55,110 --> 00:25:56,480
I'll be ready,sir.

447
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:59,240
Good,because you'll be
the first female homicide detective

448
00:25:59,241 --> 00:26:00,841
in the Philly Police Department.

449
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:03,040
You're gonna need a thick skin.

450
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:05,200
I can handle myself.

451
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,750
I knew that a long time ago.

452
00:26:28,610 --> 00:26:30,640
There was a letter sitting
on my desk. You see it ?

453
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:34,570
Nope. But I did check out the
barrack's sign-out log from '05.

454
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:37,480
- All of them?
- Hup two.

455
00:26:37,790 --> 00:26:41,020
There's only one cadet who never left
the barracks on a weekend

456
00:26:41,021 --> 00:26:42,621
his entire knob year.

457
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:44,860
Ryan Stewart.

458
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:46,820
Never even went home
for the holidays.

459
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:48,890
You should check out
his transcript.

460
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:51,320
Those marks-- it's a wonder they
let him stay at the school at all.

461
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:52,850
Rhianna had a lot of issues.

462
00:26:52,890 --> 00:26:56,890
You know, being soft, dull and friendless
is no way to go through college.

463
00:26:58,820 --> 00:27:00,660
Cadet Ryan Stewart, Philly PD.

464
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:02,820
Go away!

465
00:27:05,370 --> 00:27:06,550
There's something blocking it.

466
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:07,930
Open the door, you little pissant.

467
00:27:07,970 --> 00:27:10,630
