522
00:30:02,950 --> 00:30:04,100
No. I didn't say that.

523
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:05,790
No. You think that. Right ?

524
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:07,800
They all think it.

525
00:30:09,130 --> 00:30:10,900
You-you know that the guys
above us...

526
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:13,600
they all say that they're the last
true class of PMI because of you.

527
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:17,060
- Not 'cause of me.
- You have ruined everything.

528
00:30:17,770 --> 00:30:19,690
Graduating from here
used to mean something.

529
00:30:19,750 --> 00:30:22,130
- Ryan, just take the notes.
- No, I don't want the notes.

530
00:30:22,560 --> 00:30:23,930
Damn it, Ryan.

531
00:30:31,660 --> 00:30:36,120
And I just kept waiting
for her to stand up...

532
00:30:39,020 --> 00:30:40,710
...but she didn't.

533
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:43,810
How did you get rid of the body ?

534
00:30:45,380 --> 00:30:47,500
What ?

535
00:30:50,870 --> 00:30:53,350
You were a freshman.
You didn't have a car.

536
00:30:53,390 --> 00:30:56,220
