560
00:32:18,790 --> 00:32:21,070
Yeah, but you promoted
that chucklehead.

561
00:32:21,110 --> 00:32:23,310
Got your sigture on his evaluations.

562
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:26,220
"Cadet Stewart shows promise."

563
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:28,120
You saying I gave him a pass,
Detective ?

564
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:29,930
That what it sounds like to you ?

565
00:32:30,010 --> 00:32:32,950
Took another look at
those campus car records.

566
00:32:33,030 --> 00:32:36,530
Every Sunday morning, it was you
who checked out one of those cars.

567
00:32:36,570 --> 00:32:38,410
I take my mother to mass
on Sundays.

568
00:32:38,490 --> 00:32:40,030
A diligent son.

569
00:32:40,100 --> 00:32:41,790
Well,it turns out you're
a creature of habit.

570
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:44,080
You got three speeding tickets,
two on the 76,

571
00:32:44,081 --> 00:32:45,481
and another on Ridge Avenue.

572
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,740
Same car.

573
00:32:46,790 --> 00:32:48,050
I like to be on time.

574
00:32:48,130 --> 00:32:51,490
See,Ridge Ave off 76 goes
right through Roxborough.

575
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:54,230
And the cemetery where Kate
Butler's body was buried.

576
00:32:54,270 --> 00:32:56,370
Now you're saying I had
something to do

577
00:32:56,371 --> 00:32:57,971
with Cadet Butler's murder ?

578
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:59,580
Told you,
Lawrence drove that car.

579
00:32:59,620 --> 00:33:01,820
Lawrence was just the
clerk who knew too much.

580
00:33:01,860 --> 00:33:03,900
Knew about the doctored
sign-out logs from the barracks.

581
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:05,590
Lawrence Gardner was unstable.

582
00:33:05,630 --> 00:33:08,490
What you wanted us to think when you
stuffed the car keys in his pocket.

583
00:33:08,530 --> 00:33:10,510
Teach you that in
hand-to-hand combat training,

584
00:33:10,511 --> 00:33:13,411
how to kill a man in his sleep,
string him up ?

585
00:33:14,710 --> 00:33:16,200
Pretty fanciful.

586
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:17,770
Yeah.

587
00:33:17,890 --> 00:33:20,830
Same way you panicked when
my partner got too close.

588
00:33:20,870 --> 00:33:23,230
Ran her off the road
in that same car.

589
00:33:26,980 --> 00:33:29,370
What happened between
Cadets Stewart and Butler

590
00:33:29,371 --> 00:33:31,371
was tragic and shameful,

591
00:33:31,410 --> 00:33:33,420
but if you're looking
to spread the blame,

592
00:33:33,421 --> 00:33:35,221
I suggest you start
with the courts.

593
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:37,520
The courts...

594
00:33:38,620 --> 00:33:39,650
killed Kate Butler ?

595
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:42,300
Do you know how many congressmen
have graduated from PMI ?

596
00:33:42,380 --> 00:33:46,660
Twelve. Six senators,
eight four-star generals.

597
00:33:46,930 --> 00:33:50,930
Those courts ordered us to
change the way we do things here.

598
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:53,570
Now here we are.

599
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:56,940
Stuck installing women's
latrines and tampon dispensers.

600
00:33:56,970 --> 00:34:00,270
There are over 60 women's
colleges in this country.

601
00:34:00,350 --> 00:34:03,290
Do you see any men banging
down the doors trying to get in ?

602
00:34:03,330 --> 00:34:05,950
The value of a separate
education

603
00:34:06,051 --> 00:34:08,851
is that it is separate !

604
00:34:10,910 --> 00:34:12,050
Sound bitter, Moe.

605
00:34:12,090 --> 00:34:14,400
Because of this catastrophic
experiment,

606
00:34:14,401 --> 00:34:16,201
an army of lawyers and press

607
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:19,710
stand ready to shut down
the institution I love,

608
00:34:19,750 --> 00:34:24,730
the one thing I share with
my father and his before him.

609
00:34:24,930 --> 00:34:30,420
Excuse me if I forgot to shed a
tear for Hank Butler's daughter.

610
00:34:31,210 --> 00:34:33,640
That why you buried her ?

611
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:42,190
Think I'll take one
of those lawyers now.

612
00:35:04,230 --> 00:35:06,040
Long night ?

613
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:10,350
Can't piece it together.

614
00:35:11,650 --> 00:35:13,530
The story.

615
00:35:15,730 --> 00:35:17,770
What you always told me.

616
00:35:18,130 --> 00:35:20,720
Ask the right questions
till the story makes sense.

617
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:24,410
So what's the right question ?

618
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:36,070
You remember the honor code,
Ryan ?

619
00:35:36,420 --> 00:35:40,540
"A cadet shall not lie, cheat, or steal,
nor tolerate those who do."

620
00:35:40,580 --> 00:35:42,760
- He.
- What ?

621
00:35:42,761 --> 00:35:44,661
"Nor shall
he tolerate those who do."

622
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:47,620
That's right, by and for men,

623
00:35:47,721 --> 00:35:51,021
the way it's always been,
the way Moe wants it to stay.

624
00:35:51,940 --> 00:35:54,720
See, Moe believed in me.

625
00:35:55,660 --> 00:35:57,580
Still worried he'll think less of you ?

626
00:35:57,620 --> 00:35:59,390
That you're not a man if
you don't take the rap ?

627
00:35:59,430 --> 00:36:01,120
Not PMI material ?

628
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,290
The school has a tradition.

629
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:04,550
It has a code.

630
00:36:04,590 --> 00:36:06,710
That's what he'd have you believe.

631
00:36:06,790 --> 00:36:10,160
But if the honor code
is the backbone of PMI...

632
00:36:11,660 --> 00:36:14,050
why did he ask you to lie ?

633
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:23,290
Lawrence Gardner didn't
kill himself, did he ?

634
00:36:23,370 --> 00:36:26,240
No,he didn't,Ryan.

635
00:36:26,470 --> 00:36:28,790
I went to tell him what I did wrong.

636
00:36:28,850 --> 00:36:30,600
I didn't know what else to do.

637
00:36:30,740 --> 00:36:34,580
<i>"Immortality" by Pearl Jam.</i>

638
00:36:35,370 --> 00:36:36,690
You'd better have
a hell of a good reason

639
00:36:36,691 --> 00:36:38,391
for bothering me
on a Saturday night,boy.

640
00:36:38,430 --> 00:36:40,550
I hurt her, sir.

641
00:36:42,020 --> 00:36:43,510
Get in here.

642
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:48,740
Get a hold of yourself, cadet.
Who did you hurt ?

643
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:50,510
Cadet Butler,sir.

644
00:36:50,550 --> 00:36:52,200
I hit her and she didn't get up.

645
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:53,290
Where is she ?

646
00:36:53,380 --> 00:36:54,930
In her room.
She's not breathing, sir.

647
00:36:55,010 --> 00:36:56,110
What do you mean
she's not breathing ?

648
00:36:56,190 --> 00:36:58,470
I didn't mean it,sir.

649
00:37:04,750 --> 00:37:05,730
Who else knows ?

650
00:37:05,770 --> 00:37:07,700
Came straight to you, sir.

651
00:37:18,140 --> 00:37:20,460
You want to graduate from
this institution, don't you, son ?

652
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:21,870
More than anything, sir.

653
00:37:21,910 --> 00:37:23,440
Be a PMI man just like
your father ?

654
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:25,450
- Sir, yes, sir.
- Good.

655
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:30,200
Go get a footlocker out of storage.

656
00:37:34,310 --> 00:37:37,870
This did not happen,
not on this campus.

657
00:37:37,910 --> 00:37:40,150
Do you understand me, son ?!

658
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:42,230
Loud and clear, sir.

659
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,460
As you were.

660
00:37:48,740 --> 00:37:50,860
Sir, yes, sir.

661
00:37:57,610 --> 00:37:59,420
Got you,Moe.

662
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:01,810
That so ?

663
00:38:02,750 --> 00:38:04,550
You sent Ryan for that footlocker,

664
00:38:04,651 --> 00:38:08,951
made Cadet Butler's body disappear,
and you framed Lawrence for the job.

665
00:38:10,390 --> 00:38:12,800
What,now you going to tell
me that kid is really dead?

666
00:38:14,990 --> 00:38:20,370
I just... I just know he didn't do it.

667
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:23,580
That's all that matters.

668
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:25,820
Stories.

669
00:38:26,530 --> 00:38:29,630
You're just telling yourself stories.

670
00:38:32,030 --> 00:38:33,990
Even tried to take out a cop.

671
00:38:34,070 --> 00:38:34,710
You ?

672
00:38:34,711 --> 00:38:38,611
Busier than a one-legged man
in an ass-kicking competition, Moe.

673
00:38:41,590 --> 00:38:45,750
You can only keep the flood
back for so long, Detective.

674
00:38:46,850 --> 00:38:49,050
The flood ?

675
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:51,310
Pretty soon it's going
to pull you down...

676
00:38:52,711 --> 00:38:54,111
for good.

677
00:39:00,510 --> 00:39:02,780
You put that girl in a box !

678
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:08,840
I put you there, too, sweetheart.

679
00:39:22,710 --> 00:39:25,850
No. No, I got out.

680
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,970
I got you !

681
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:31,780
Not from where I'm sitting.

682
00:39:46,020 --> 00:39:48,410
What the hell is going on ?!

683
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:57,770
<i>Long as you ask the right
questions, never too late.</i>

684
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:37,080
It's okay, Lil.
It's going to be okay.

685
00:40:37,130 --> 00:40:39,710
We're going to get this guy,
all right, we'll get him.

686
00:40:39,830 --> 00:40:43,050
EMT said she kept going on
about the barracks sign-out log.

687
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:45,280
Just located the car
that ran her off the road.

688
00:40:45,330 --> 00:40:47,520
On campus.

689
00:40:50,870 --> 00:40:55,150
<i>Dear Lilly, there are two sides
to every story,</i>

690
00:40:55,151 --> 00:40:59,451
<i>neither of which I think
you'll find satisfactory.</i>

691
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:04,940
<i>Suffice it to say, there is no way I could
have stayed with your mother and survived.</i>

692
00:41:05,060 --> 00:41:08,710
<i>In that sense,
you're already stronger than me.</i>

693
00:41:08,830 --> 00:41:10,790
<i>"Black" by Pearl Jam.</i>

694
00:41:10,830 --> 00:41:13,770
<i>I was a lousy father.</i>

695
00:41:13,930 --> 00:41:16,520
<i>When I got sober enough to
figure out how much I missed,</i>

696
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:19,310
<i>it was too late
to undo the damage.</i>

697
00:41:19,390 --> 00:41:26,440
* Sheets of empty
canvas Untouched sheets *

698
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:28,560
<i>Much to my regret,</i>

699
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,790
<i>I'll always be the dad
who bought you a bike,</i>

700
00:41:31,870 --> 00:41:34,300
<i>but never taught you
how to ride it.</i>

701
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:40,530
* Spread out before me
As her body once did *

702
00:41:44,020 --> 00:41:45,650
<i>There were a few moments</i>

703
00:41:45,850 --> 00:41:48,480
<i>I tried to reconnect along the way.</i>

704
00:41:49,300 --> 00:41:54,050
<i>But you were on your own
path by then, your own woman.</i>

705
00:41:54,330 --> 00:41:56,410
<i>And you turned out great, kid.</i>

706
00:41:57,010 --> 00:42:00,530
*****

